ments provinciaux. Les auteurs analysent la façon particulière dont le Sénat exerce ses pouvoirs législatifs par rapport à la Chambre des communes. Ils évaluent également la contribution de la Chambre haute à la formulation et à la révision des politiques en illustrant comment il sert de tribune utile à représenter les divers intérêts régionaux, linguistiques, culturels et socioéconomiques du Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAjzenstat, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranks, C.E.S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoyal, Serge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurray, Lowell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagle, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRémillard, Gil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, David E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStilborn, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomas, Paul G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatts, Ronald L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357163140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773571631423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773571631/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-1